cs.MA, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.RO 

The paper discusses the use of a multi-agent approach to model the behaviour of slime mould for unconventional computing. This involves the use of computational mechanisms and the application of spatial concentration gradients to influence the behaviour of the material. This topic is likely to fall under the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper explicitly mentions the use of a multi-agent approach to model the behaviour of slime mould. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The use of a living embodied computational material and the adaptation of collective transport networks may be relevant to this sub-category. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the use of a virtual computing material that can be influenced by external stimuli, which may be relevant to AI. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The discussion of emergent properties such as relaxation and minimisation may be relevant to this sub-category. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The potential applications of the approach for path planning and data smoothing may be relevant to robotics.
